quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  52,32,Enjoin them their understandings to this? or are they a people conumacious
  52,33,"Or say they: he hath fabricated it: aye they will not believe"
  52,34,"Let them bring a discourse like thereUnto, if they say sooth"
  52,35,"Have they not been created by aught, or are they the creators"
  52,36,Created they the heavens and the earth! Aye! they will not be convinced
  52,37,Are with them the treasures of thy Lord! or are they the dispensers
  52,38,Have they a stairway whereby they overhear? Then let their listener bring an authority manifest
  52,39,Hath He daughters and ye sons
  52,40,Or askest thou a hire from them so that they are with debt laden
  52,41,"Is with them the Unseen, and they write it down"
  52,42,Seek they to lay a plot? Then those who disbelieve it is they who shall be plotted against
  52,43,Is theirs a god beside Allah? Hallowed be Allah from that which they associate
  52,44,"And if they should see a fragment of the heaven falling down, they would say: it is only clouds piled up"
  52,45,"Wherefore let them alone, till they meet their Day whereon they shall swoon"
  52,46,"A Day whereon their plotting will avail them not at all, nor will they be succoured"
  52,47,And verily for those who do wrong there is a torment before that; but most of them know not
  52,48,And wait thou patiently the judgment of thy Lord; verily thou art before Our eyes; and hallow the praise of thy Lord when thou uprisest
  52,49,"And in the night also hallow Him, and at the setting of the stars"